observations.recommendation:
We have recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

determine the amount of unexpended current year disaster funds, except those for capital outlay, to be transferred to the Special Trust Fund and recognize the same as Trust Liabilities - Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund at year-end;

recognize calamity-driven cash donations in the Trust Liabilities - Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund account;


not recognize in the books of accounts calamity-driven in-kind donations; and


revise the current subsidiary ledgers to comply with the accounting guidelines which is based on source and year for unexpended disaster funds in the Special Trust Fund and based on source and purpose for cash donations while considering whether the donated amount is ₱100,000.00 and above or below ₱100,000.00.

We have recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

present the Notes to Financial Statements in comparative figures and information;


present the aging analysis of the receivable accounts defined as financial assets;

provide the disclosure requirements in COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014 for the Trust Liabilities - Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund account and the Inventories and Property, Plant and Equipment related to the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund (LDRRMF);

for each class of Property, Plant and Equipment, disclose the estimated useful life used in calculating the corresponding depreciation expense, the gross carrying amount and the accumulated depreciation at the beginning and end of the period, and a reconciliation of the carrying amount at the beginning and end of the period;

present the reconciliation between Actual Amounts in the SCBAA with that of the Statement of Financial Performance; and

provide disclosures for Financial Instruments as required in IPSAS 30 which were already presented in COA Circular No. 2016-004 dated September 30, 2016 for update.

