We have recommended the Municipal Mayor to require the Municipal Accountant to:

a. coordinate with the Engineering office and Assessor’s Office for the revaluation of the useful life of the road network asset taking into consideration the design and usage of the same;

b. re-compute the depreciation and accumulated depreciation for the road network by disregarding the 5% residual value; 

c. observe the disclosure requirements in the preparation financial statements in accordance with PPSAS 17 and COA Circular 2015-008; and

d. reclassify the two noted gravelling projects totaling P105,868.38 as a prior years’ expense rather than as part of the road network asset.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor enforce strict implementation of the provisions of RA No. 9003 by carrying out the following:

a. Request the legislative body to enact ordinance on the mandatory segregation of wastes, amend the obsolete “no littering” ordinance, and other related ordinances that will support the resilient enforcement of SWM and other environmental laws;

b. Procure protective gears for the garbage collectors and provide insurance that will safeguard their health; 

c. Establish close coordination with the barangay officials to ensure that efforts to improve the municipal SWM will reach the barangay level; and.

d. Sustain what has been put in place to carry out the law and to think of ways to further improve their programs, projects and activities for better protection of the environment and the general welfare of the public.

We recommended that Management:

a. Recognize the fund transfers as receivable from PO and a payable to the national government by requiring the Municipal Accountant to record it in the books of the Municipality;

b. Communicate with the officials of the People’s Organization to submit Fund Utilization Reports of all completed and accomplished projects and activities as basis for recording the liquidation of fund;

We have recommended
Management to:
a. cause the installation of float valves w/ accessories at Caragasan and Calupaan on the project Improvement/Construction of Water System/Reservoir;
b. remove and replace the identified one span of concrete pavement with major scaling amounting to P19,202.40 and the multiple cracks noted in two spans of concrete pavement amounting to P38,404.80 on the project Concreting of Junction to Caragasan Access Road;
c. inform the contractors to implement corrective measures on defects noted on the project Construction of Centralized Market Building to prevent further deterioration of the structure; and
d. justify the delays noted in the project completion.

We recommended that Management:
a. Recognize the fund transfers as receivable from PO and a payable to the national government by requiring the Municipal Accountant to record it in the books of the Municipality;
b. Communicate with the officials of the People’s Organization to submit Fund Utilization Reports of all completed and accomplished projects and activities as basis for recording the liquidation of fund;
c. Direct the Municipal Accountant to record all funds received and utilized.
